				<article id="post-4" class="post-4 page type-page status-publish hentry post">

					<div class="entry-main">

						
						<div class="entry-content">
							<div id="pl-4"><div class="panel-grid" id="pg-4-0" ><div class="panel-grid-cell" id="pgc-4-0-0" ><div class="so-panel widget widget_bcn_widget widget_breadcrumb_navxt panel-first-child panel-last-child" id="panel-4-0-0-0" data-index="0"><div class="breadcrumbs" vocab="http://schema.org/" typeof="BreadcrumbList"><!-- Breadcrumb NavXT 5.4.0 -->
<span property="itemListElement" typeof="ListItem"><a property="item" typeof="WebPage" title="Go to POPP Communications." href="http://popp.com" class="main-home"><span property="name">POPP Communications</span></a><meta property="position" content="1"></span> &gt; <span property="itemListElement" typeof="ListItem"><span property="name">Employment</span><meta property="position" content="2"></span></div></div></div></div><div class="panel-grid" id="pg-4-1" ><div class="panel-grid-cell" id="pgc-4-1-0" ><div class="so-panel widget widget_sow-editor panel-first-child panel-last-child" id="panel-4-1-0-0" data-index="1"><div class="so-widget-sow-editor so-widget-sow-editor-base">
<div class="siteorigin-widget-tinymce textwidget">
	<h1>WORKING AT POPP COMMUNICATIONS</h1>
<p><strong>OUR CORE VALUES</strong></p>
<p>Our core values define who we are and how we serve clients. They guide us on our journey as we improve ourselves and contribute to the greater good.</p>
<p><strong>Client Focused </strong><br />
Client Focused means we listen to clearly understand our clients' needs and put our minds to work to serve clients. As Client Focused team members, we:</p>
<ul>
<li>Consider the impact to clients in all we do</li>
<li>Connect with clients, own the moment, and make good things happen</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Process Driven </strong><br />
Processes enable each team member to confidently make promises and consistently deliver, resulting in high trust and confidence. As team members committed to Process, we:</p>
<ul>
<li>Understand the power of process and how it helps us collaborate, use time efficiently, and guides us to win/win results</li>
<li>Know following processes requires discipline and fanatical attention to details</li>
<li>Are empowered to make suggestions to improve processes</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Professionals </strong><br />
Professionals understand that productivity, accountability, and exceeding client expectations is how we win. As Professionals, we:</p>
<ul>
<li>Listen to understand, clarify, weigh, and prioritize before making a decision</li>
<li>Gather, record, and use information that is current, accurate, and relevant to set the stage for future success</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Productive Attitudes </strong><br />
When we all bring Productive Attitudes to work we create an environment that is successful and fun. Productive Attitudes, Habits, and Enthusiasm happen when we:</p>
<ul>
<li>Consistently contribute to client and team success</li>
<li>Are accountable to accomplish our roles, responsibilities, and goals</li>
<li>Practice professional persistence to create win/win results</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Do the Right Thing</strong><br />
As POPP people, we Do the Right Thing because everything we do is for someone and we know that Doing the Right Thing continuously builds trust and confidence. Doing the Right Thing means we:</p>
<ul>
<li>Continuously learn and improve because knowledge is a competitive advantage</li>
<li>Accept responsibility for quality and productivity</li>
<li>Manage first things first, make good decisions, and use time wisely</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>OUR BENEFITS</strong></p>
<p>POPP team members receive a comprehensive benefits package that includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>Paid Holidays</li>
<li>Paid Time Off (PTO)</li>
<li>Company Events</li>
<li>Employee Discounts</li>
<li>Employer Matched 401(k) Plan</li>
<li>529 College Savings Plan</li>
<li>Tuition Reimbursement</li>
<li>Length of Service Award</li>
<li>Flexible Savings Accounts</li>
<li>Medical | Dental insurance</li>
<li>Company Paid Life Insurance</li>
<li>Voluntary Life Insurance</li>
<li>Short Term Disability</li>
<li>Family &amp; Medical Leave</li>
<li>Maternity | Paternity | Adoption Leave</li>
<li>Bereavement Leave</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>OUR HIRING PROCESS</strong></p>
<p>Our selection process is designed to find the right fit for both candidates and POPP.</p>
<p><strong>1. Submit Your Resume</strong></p>
<p>Apply now by submitting a copy of your resume to <a href="mailto:recruiter@popp.com">recruiter@popp.com</a>. Please include the position name in the subject line of the email. All resumes are reviewed within four weeks of receipt. Candidates not contacted within four weeks, will have their resume kept on file for one year.</p>
<p><strong>2. Phone Screen</strong></p>
<p>Candidates may receive the opportunity to discuss their qualifications further via a brief phone conversation with a recruiter. Next steps will be shared with the candidate during the phone conversation.</p>
<p><strong>3. First Interview</strong></p>
<p>Professional business attire is appropriate for on-site interviews. Ample parking is available for free on site. Use the building’s center entrance marked ‘Main’. Our reception area is through the door on the left.</p>
<p>Candidates will complete an application for employment. A copy of the candidate’s resume and references will be helpful in completing the application.</p>
<p>Candidates should expect to learn next steps from a Recruiter within two weeks of your interview.</p>
<p><strong>4. Next Steps</strong></p>
<p>Up to three interviews may be conducted during the interview process. POPP provides candidates an opportunity to meet with a variety of POPP team members, including a recruiter, hiring manager, and vice president &amp; general manager. Candidates may also have the opportunity to job shadow a POPP team member performing the same or similar function.</p>
<p>Professional and personal references are conducted.</p>
<p>Candidates should expect to learn next steps or a final decision from a Recruiter within two weeks of their interview.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
